T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
JA  - International Economic Review
SP  - 2019
EP  - 2046
VL  - 65
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12710
Y2  - 2026/04/24
N2  - Abstract Add ons are features or services that can enhance the functionality or quality of base goods. They are pervasive. Yet we know little about the behavior of add-on prices over the business cycle. We use 10 years of data from a nationwide Canadian retailer to investigate the local cyclicality of extended warranty prices, a classic add on. We find base prices are acyclical. Warranty prices are procyclical because local stores use warranties to make demand for durable goods less price-elastic. We show add ons amplify responses to national business cycles and study the implications for inflation rate bias.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - RAZOR-THIN MASS ELECTIONS WITH HIGH TURNOUT
AU  - Levine, David K.
AU  - Martinelli, Cesar
Y1  - 2024/11/01
PY  - 2024
DA  - 2024/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12711
